The temporalCoverage of a DataCatalog indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in ISO 8601 time interval format.

The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a DataCatalog, it indicates areas that the DataCatalog describes: a DataCatalog of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

A schema describing a sample the Center for Viral Systems Biology. Primary samples = blood draw, tissue sample, urine, or feces.  Derived are some sort of isolation/preparation of whole blood/tissue, e.g. plasma, sera, DNA, RNA, etc.
unique ID for the derived sample; ideally, the combination of sampleType and isolationDate. Should not contain non-public IDs
Alternate identifers for sample. Can contain private IDs.
Descriptive name of the derived sample
Short description of the derived sample
Unique public patient id
Visit code for the patient (day post hospitalization of blood draw for patients, visit number after initial for follow-up/contact)
Date of sample creation/collection (NOT date of blood draw/tissue collection, unless the sample is that primary sample) (YYYY-MM-DD)

Sample type. Primary types: "blood_purple-EDTA", "blood_blue-citrate", "blood_mixed", "blood_unknown", "urine", "feces", "organs", "tissue"; Derived types: "plasma", "serum", "buffy coat", "PBMC", "frozenPBMC-DNA", "frozenPBMC-RNA", "viralRNA", "totalRNA", "DNA"
Integer expressing how far derived the sample is from the primary sample.  Primary sample (e.g. blood draw) has a derivedIndex=0; PBMC=1, ...
Source of sample (human or rat)
Protocol version to isolate sample; either file name and/or version
Link to protocol used to isolate sample
What buffer was used to freeze the sample in; relevant for PBMC samples
How much a plamsa sample has been diluted from its original isolation
Whether a plasma or serum sample is AVL-inactivated
Current location(s) for the sample, including Lab, number of aliquots, and when the info was last updated
Date of last update (YYYY-MM-DD)
Version number of sample, auto-assigned by CViSB database
A schema describing a the location of a sample in the Center for Viral Systems Biology
Current location of sample
Number of aliquots for a particular sampleID at a particular lab location. If sample has been used up, numAliquots = 0
Date of last update (YYYY-MM-DD)
Person who updated the sample location
